'''Soul Tree''' (Japanese: {{Lang|jp|ソウルツリー}}, ''sourutsurī'') is a game mechanic in {{XC3}}. It unlocks upgrades for the main characters' [[Ouroboros]] forms, unlocking and enhancing [[Battle Arts (XC3)|Arts]] and [[Skill (XC3)|Skills]] innate to their Ouroboros. It is comparable to the [[Skill Tree]] in {{XC}} and the [[Affinity Chart (XC2)|Affinity Chart]] in {{XC2}}.
== Overview == The Soul Tree is unlocked for Keves party members at the end of Chapter 2, as they unlock their Ouroboros forms then. The Agnus party members unlock their own Soul Trees at the end of Chapter 3.
Upgrades in the Soul Tree require '''Soul Points''', or '''SP'''. Soul Points can be earned by various means, such as opening [[Container]]s, completing {{Link noparens|Quest (XC3)}}s, or defeating {{Link noparens|Unique Monster (XC3)}}s. In order to unlock a node containing an ability, an adjacent node's ability must be acquired. For enhancing arts and skills, the base art or skill must already be learned in order to acquire the upgrade.
Once all Ouroboros forms have been unlocked, stat increases, Heat Gauge upgrades and skills in one's Soul Tree may be shared with their Ouroboros partner, in a process known as '''Soul Link'''. Initially only one slot is available to Soul Link, with the second slot being unlocked upon completing that character's Side Story. == Gallery == <gallery> File:XC3 Soul Tree Noah.jpeg|The Soul Tree of Noah's Ouroboros File:XC3 Soul Tree Mio.jpeg|The Soul Tree of Mio's Ouroboros File:XC3 Soul Tree Eunie.jpeg|The Soul Tree of Eunie's Ouroboros File:XC3 Soul Tree Taion.jpeg|The Soul Tree of Taion's Ouroboros File:XC3 Soul Tree Lanz.jpeg|The Soul Tree of Lanz's Ouroboros File:XC3 Soul Tree Sena.jpeg|The Soul Tree of Sena's Ouroboros </gallery>{{clr}}
